Update style and revert moving default session initialisation

Fix issue where JSON.parse(undefined) throws exception

Observed an error "unexpected token u" on an Android WebView, searched around a little, and discovered JSON.parse with undefined can cause issues on some browsers: http://stackoverflow.com/a/13022566

Patch for <IE9 browsers

When addtohomescreen.js is used in bundle with other javascript files for web application also supporting <IE9, it will throw an exception due to "addEventListener" not being supported, blocking following code execution. This patch will also prevent useless overhead since those browsers are not mobile capable.
Merge branch 'translation/fr_fr' of https://github.com/chok/add-to-homescreen into chok-translation/fr_fr

Extended DOM ready check

Make DOM ready check work when load event has already fired. This allows addToHomescreen to be called later on, e.g. as a RequireJS module.
Otherwise a call to show will infinitely repeat and never succeed.
